entries.name: L2ERC20Gateway
entries.description: Counterpart to the L1ERC20Gateway. Can mint (deposit to L2) and burn (withdraw to L1) ERC20 tokens on L2.

entries.name: ConstitutionHash
entries.description: Keeps the current hash of the ArbitrumDAO Constitution. Settable by the L2UpgradeExecutor.

entries.name: L2SurplusFee
entries.description: This contract receives all SurplusFees: Transaction fee component that covers the cost beyond that covered by the L2 Base Fee during chain congestion. They are withdrawable to a configurable set of recipients.

recipientsData.description: Lists recipients and weights using events, while the latest represents the current state.

entries.name: L2Timelock
entries.description: Delays constitutional AIPs from the CoreGovernor by 8d.

issuedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.
manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.

Executor.description: Executing proposals is only open to all addresses if this resolves to the 0x0 address

receivedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.

entries.name: L2DAIGateway
entries.description: Counterpart to the L1DaiGateway. Can mint (deposit to L2) and burn (withdraw to L1) DAI tokens on L2.

entries.name: L2GatewayRouter
entries.description: Router managing token <–> gateway mapping on L2.

entries.name: L2WethGateway
entries.description: Counterpart to the Bridge on L1. Mints and burns WETH on L2.

entries.name: L2LPTGateway
entries.description: Counterpart to the L1LPTGateway. Can mint (deposit to L2) and burn (withdraw to L1) LPT on L2.

entries.name: TreasuryGovernor
entries.description: Governance contract used for creating non-constitutional AIPs, or “treasury proposals”, e.g., transferring founds out of the DAO Treasury. Also enforces the 3% quorum for proposals.

l2TreasuryQuorumPercent.description: The percentage of the total supply that is required to pass a proposal.

entries.name: L2ArbitrumToken
entries.description: The ARB token contract. Supply can be increased by the owner once per year by a maximum of 2%.

mintCapPerYer.description: The percentage of the total supply that can be minted by the owner once per year.

entries.name: SecurityCouncilMemberSyncAction
entries.description: Contract used by the security council management system to sync SecurityCouncil members between the L1 and the L2.

entries.name: L2BaseFee
entries.description: This contract receives all BaseFees: The transaction fee component that covers the minimum cost of Arbitrum transaction execution. They are withdrawable to a configurable set of recipients.

recipientsData.description: Lists recipients and weights using events, while the latest represents the current state.

entries.name: TreasuryTimelock
entries.description: Delays treasury proposals from the TreasuryGovernor by 259200 seconds. Is used as the main recipient for the ETH from L2SurplusFee and L2BaseFee contracts.

entries.name: L2ARBGateway
entries.description: ARB sent from L2 to L1 is escrowed in this contract and minted on L1.

entries.name: L2UpgradeExecutor
entries.description: This contract can upgrade the L2 system's contracts through the L2ProxyAdmin. The upgrades can be done either by the Security Council or by the L1Timelock (via its alias on L2).

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.

entries.name: SecurityCouncilManager
entries.description: This contract enforces the rules for changing members and cohorts of the SecurityCouncil and creates crosschain messages to Ethereum and Arbitrum Nova to keep the configuration in sync.

getBothCohorts.description: All 12 addresses of the 2 cohorts of the SecurityCouncil (2x6)

entries.name: CoreGovernor
entries.description: Governance contract accepting and managing constitutional Arbitrum Improvement Proposals (AIPs, core proposals) and, among other formal parameters, enforcing the 5% quorum for proposals.

l2CoreQuorumPercent.description: The percentage of the total supply that is required to pass a proposal.

receivedPermissions.description: manage all access control roles and change the minimum delay.
